# <%= packageName %>

> <%= description %>

A skills module built on [@14e-inc/comfy-skills](https://github.com/hebronwatson/comfyjs/tree/main/packages/comfy-skills).
Importing this package auto-registers its skills into the shared `globalRegistry`.

## Install

```sh
npm install <%= packageName %> @14e-inc/comfy-skills
```

## Usage

```ts
// Side-effect import registers all skills into globalRegistry
import '<%= packageName %>';
import { globalRegistry } from '@14e-inc/comfy-skills';

const result = await globalRegistry.run('<%= skillSlug %>', { message: 'hello' });
console.log(result);
```

You can also import skills directly:

```ts
import { <%= skillCamel %>Skill } from '<%= packageName %>';

const output = await <%= skillCamel %>Skill.execute({ message: 'hello' });
```
